chapter:
Description of the ALFS profile syntax



ALFS profiles are written using an XML syntax. This chapter describes 
the various XML elements that can occur in the profile.


For each element, one describes :




the formal definition of the element, using the DTD 
syntax


a description of the element


one or several examples


the equivalent bash scripts for the examples, when 
applicable






The bash scripts have been generated by YAALFS. The checking of the 
return code have been removed.


This document describes the syntax of the version 3.1 of the 
syntax, as used in nALFS 1.1.8 and YAALFS.


